*************High-Availability VMware Server Cluster*********************

Establish a connection to the Bonn-Rhein University web server,  remotely via OpenVPN

Through the vSphere Web Client at https://10.20.108.209/ui/?locale=en_US 

Choosing "SMG Cluster" as compute resource, with the Selection of "Thin Provision" as virtual disk format, "Datastore Default" as storage policy and "Praktikum" as datastore.

The new VM is then selected from the panel "VM Hardware"

The virtual machine is suspended and once completed power it back on, continue observing the
ping output, and the “Fault Tolerance” is observed. Finally clone to the Virtual Machine and further changes were observed.
